The paper deals with the capacity region of a fading multiple access channel with distributed CSI and power control, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of block-fading and the consideration of slow-fading links suggest a possible connection to networked systems (cs.NI). The analysis of the adaptive capacity region and the optimal rate allocation function are related to control and optimization (cs.SY). The consideration of arbitrary fading distributions and the characterization of optimal power control suggest a possible connection to mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Finally, the topic of multiple access channels and power control also has relevance to communication systems (cs.COM).
